citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-01-15T15:17:03.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-01-15T15:27:32.000Z","msg":"戇撚鳩鳩，咪話陳浩天嚮抗共上嘅貢獻大過班食塞米嘅飯民"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-01-15T15:31:44.000Z","msg":"He arrived for his interview in spectacles and a white shirt, looking like any young office worker on the streets of Hong Kong&rsquo;s central business district&mdash;except that he is jobless save for the occasional gig in interior design. Over the course of two hours, the business and engineering graduate was unable to describe the roadmap by which Hong Kong could achieve independence or defend itself against China. He offered no picture of what an independent Hong Kong might look and feel like, who its international allies might be, who would lead it, or how that leader might be chosen. He could not name an author or a historical Hong Kong figure who inspired him politically. He spoke warmly but without notable zeal about the territory, its people, history and culture (&ldquo;I don&rsquo;t know, I just feel like Hong Kong is such a great place; it&rsquo;s my home&rdquo;). In fact, he became most animated when talking about the year he spent as a transfer student in Uppsala University. &ldquo;Oh, Sweden!&rdquo; he said, brightly. &ldquo;Sweden is much better than Hong Kong.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nNeither could he offer any dramatic account of political awakening or the coalescing of a Hong Kong identity. When pressed about the former he says, fairly bloodlessly, that he attended the Umbrella Revolution protests, and could feel &ldquo;something wrong with Hong Kong,&rdquo; but described no eureka moment when he vowed to dedicate his life to the struggle and could not convincingly say why anybody should be expected to take such risks. When pressed on identity, he said that at Uppsala he began drawing a distinction between Hong Kong and China when other students asked where he was from. But thousands of young Hongkongers studying abroad make the same distinction without becoming revolutionaries and independence activists.<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e0e45a562da0f4181652a6fc713d18e75196528f","tid":981180,"uid":30988,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"9594020afdc3d4fab69509ac0b2fd818a538b1e6","tid":981180,"uid":93043,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"quote":{"pid":"7294aa88b1524578f984ac961239fa8c54f5ae51","tid":981180,"uid":30988,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"2418eb0b832840c32848b218a395fd21b7334c1f","tid":981180,"uid":93043,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-01-15T15:17:03.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-01-15T15:27:32.000Z","msg":"戇撚鳩鳩，咪話陳浩天嚮抗共上嘅貢獻大過班食塞米嘅飯民"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-01-15T15:30:15.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-01-15T15:38:01.000Z","msg":"馬凱事件嘛，FCC 嘛，答咗囉盲毛 <img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n有用過班白出糧泛民多多聲啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"90dfa522270373518acc7eb09d105f04903e8ee5","tid":981180,"uid":93043,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-01-15T15:48:19.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"dc2761d1fdd2198c2a91f45f1e62069d037fdaaf","tid":981180,"uid":81518,"like":2,"dislike":2,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-01-15T15:56:42.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"3e34a46746ac9d4f06ffd73f80ab36861694e391","tid":981180,"uid":12367,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"quote":{"pid":"dc2761d1fdd2198c2a91f45f1e62069d037fdaaf","tid":981180,"uid":81518,"like":2,"dislike":2,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-01-15T15:56:42.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-01-15T16:13:10.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/qqx4dIY.gif\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.imgur.com%2Fqqx4dIY.gif&h=b976afdd&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"fa55f5fa928d56127bdd2147a0aadf36294b252d","tid":981180,"uid":30988,"like":0,"dislike":0,"